<subSubSection pageNumber="609" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="609">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="609">Note:</emphasis>
This is the 
<typeStatus>generitype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authority="Loefl." authorityName="Loefl." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Krameriaceae" genus="Krameria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zygophyllales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="609">Krameria</emphasis>
Loefl.
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="609">Iter Hisp.</emphasis>
: 195. 1758). Although some authors (e.g. Simpson in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="609">Fl. Neotropica</emphasis>
49: 81. 1989) have regarded the binomial as dating from 1758, it seems clear that &quot;Ixine Loefl.&quot; is there intended as a generic synonym of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Krameriaceae" genus="Krameria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zygophyllales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="609">Krameria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, rather than as a specific epithet to be combined with it.
</paragraph>
